definition.value: Trianion of drimenol diphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of drimenol phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
Major species at pH 7.3.
Major species at pH 7.3.
A 12 amino acid oligopeptide fragment of apelin-13 lacking the terminal L-phenylalanine residue.
A 1-hydroxy-1-phenylpropan-2-one that has (S)-configuration.
A 1-hydroxy-1-phenylpropan-2-one that has (R)-configuration. It is used as a precursor for the production of ephedrine and pseudoephedrine.
An arabinuronate that is the conjugate base of L-arabinuronic acid, obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the secondary amino function of (1S,2R)-ephedrine; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the secondary amino function of (1R,2R)-pseudoephedrine; major species at pH 7.3.
An inorganic radical cation resulting from the loss of one electron from helium-3.
An ammonium ion derivative that is the conjugate acid of (R)-methcathinone obtained from the protonation of the amino group. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
An aromatic ketone that is propiophenone in which the hydrogen alpha- to the keto group has been replaced by a methylamino group.
A 2-methylamino-1-phenylpropan-1-one that has (R)-configuration.

A tripeptide that is L-seryl-L-valyl-L-leucine in which the amino group at the N-terminal is substituted by a tert-butoxycarbonyl group and the carboxy group at the C-terminal is substituted by a {(2S,3E)-5-ethoxy-5-oxo-1-[(3S)-2-oxopyrrolidin-3-yl]pent-3-en-2-yl}amino group. It is a 3C-like protease inhibitor of MERS-CoV and SARS-CoV.

A member of the class of benzotriazoles that is 1H-benzotriazole which is substituted by a 2-oxo-2-{(4-propanamidophenyl)[(thiophen-3-yl)methyl]amino}ethyl group at position 1.  It is a 3C-like protease inhibitor of SARS-CoV and bat coronavirus HKU4.
A racemate comprising equal amounts of (R)- and (S)-methcathinone.
Compound 8a
An amino acid zwitterion obtained from the transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the amino group of D-dopa. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-L-phenylalanine where the acyl chain derives from a fatty acid, major species at pH 7.3.
A monoatomic tetracation resulting from the loss of four electrons from carbon-12.
A monoatomic hexacation resulting from the loss of six electrons from oxygen-16.

A member of the class of benzotriazoles that is 1H-benzotriazole which is substituted by a 2-{[4-(2-methylpropanamido)phenyl][(thiophen-3-yl)methyl]amino}-2-oxoethyl group at position 1. It is a 3C-like protease inhibitor of SARS-CoV and bat coronavirus HKU4.
An alpha-amino-acid residue anion resulting from the deprotonation of the 4-hydroxy group of 3-nitro-L-tyrosine residue. Major species at pH 7.3.

A member of the class of thiazolidinones that is 2-sulfanylidene-1,3-thiazolidin-4-one which is substituted at position 5 by a (4-ethylphenyl)methylidene group. It is a cell permeable inhibitor of c-Myc-Max dimerization and exhibits antitumour effects in vivo. It downregulates c-Myc expression and upregulates CDK inhibitors, p21 and p27 resulting in the inhibition of proliferation, induction of apoptosis and cell cycle arrest in G0/G1 phase.
A N-(fatty acyl)-L-serine(1-) that is the conjugate base of N-arachidonoyl-L-serine, resulting from the derotonation of the carboxy group. Major species at pH 7.3.
An N-(fatty acyl)-L-alpha-amino acid anion resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of any fatty acid with the amino group of L-serinate. Major species at pH 7.3.

A nucleobase analogue that is uracil substituted with a methyl group at position 6 and a (1E)-3-oxobut-1-en-1-yl group at position 5; one of 20 modifications to the potent microbial riboflavin-based metabolite antigen 5-(2-oxopropylideneamino)-6-D-ribityl aminouracil (5-OP-RU), an activator of mucosal-associated invariant T (MAIT) cells when presented by the MR1 protein (reported in MED:32123373).
An acyl-CoA(4-) that is the tetraanion of nicotinyl-CoA, arising from deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of nicotinyl-AMP; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of benzoyl-AMP; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of 2-pyranones that is 2H-pyran-2-one which has been substituted at positions 4 and 6 by hydroxy and pyridin-3-yl groups, respectively.
An enolate resulting from the deprotonation of the hydroxy group of 4-hydroxy-6-(pyridin-3-yl)-2H-pyran-2-one. Major species at pH 7.3.

An organic heterotetracyclic compound that is (3S,4aR,6aR,12aR,12bS)-3-hydroxy-4,4,6a,12b-tetramethyl-1,3,4,4a,5,6,6a,12,12a,12b-decahydro-2H,11H-benzo[f]pyrano[4,3-b]chromen-11-one substituted by a pyridin-3-yl group at position 9 (the 3S,4aR,6aR,12aR,12bS stereoisomer).
An antogonist that blocks chemokine receptor 2 (CCR2).
